Package org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.ltl

Enum DualMode

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<DualMode>
org.svvrl.goal.core.logic.ltl.DualMode
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DualMode>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum DualMode
extends java.lang.Enum<DualMode>
This enumeration defines two modes of duality of temporal operators. In the first mode, until (U) and unless (waitfor, W) are dual and since (S) and backto (B) are dual. In the second mode, until (U) and release (R) are dual and since (S) and trigger (T) are dual. The formula p U q is equivalent to ¬ ( (¬ p) W (¬ p ∧ ¬ q)) and ¬ ( (¬ p) R (¬ q)). For the past operators S, B, and T, the equivalent formulae are similar.
Author:
Ming-Hsien Tsai
